Title: Marvel Studios' Black Panther - Official Trailer
Comment:
PLEASE READ THIS EVERYBODY WHO CARES ABOUT THE FUTURE OF THE MCU 


This trailer is garbage, everything about it is pandering to the Black race, and the audiences that see these movies in general. this movie is a scam so that marvel can win the Black audience on top of the white audience they already have. This trailer sucks because 
1) the heavy use of rap music is just awful and in such bad taste 
2)that "secret handshake" at 0:49 seconds is also possibly the cringiest thing I've ever seen in a movie
3) it's blatantly obvious that it's narrowcasting to black people instead of a normal trailer that should just appeal to everyone 
4) the "bad guy" at 1:22 seems like the shittiest most non threatening bad guy in the MCU to date and the cringeworthy dialogue that they wrote for him and put in this trailer makes me wanna vomit 
 5) that line from 1:30 to 1:38 is possibly the most cliche line in the MCU they say that almost every movie as an illusion to make it seem like there's tension in the film but it's a lie, we all know that these heroes aren't going to die and that the world will be fine at the end of the film because this is the MCU we're talking about, where everybody lives and only quicksilver dies
6) I'm pretty sure that whole car jump thing at 1:40 was in civil war and exactly the same as it's shown here, not only is this lazy but it insulting that the Marvel company and the trailer company thought that the fans would be too stupid to notice it that we've been fed the same shit again while they take our money and show us bright colors for 2 hours 
All Of this needs to stop! We deserve better than this garbage ! Enough with this narrowcasting, enough with the fake tension and enough with these movies being lazy, uncreative and overall pandering to the audience we deserve so much better than this schlock

Title: Marvel Studios' Black Panther - Official Trailer
Comment:
Here are my speculations:

* Wakanda's technology seems to be alien-based, yet they have been hiding the technology for centuries if not millenia. Why have they been hiding their technological advanced civilization?

 * Wakanda must have received that technology from an advanced aliens; and, I suspect, Wakanda received another important gift from their alien benefactor.

* Wakanda is likely the keeper and protector of the last Infinity Gems: the Soul Gem, the only one of the six that has yet to be revealed in the MCU.

* Which explains why Wakanda has been hiding its alien-based technology - because they do not want to attract attention and invite invasion from Thanos.  If  Wakanda revealed their otherworldly technology to the world, then Thanos would find out and suspect they have an Infinity Gem.

* The event in the Black Panther movie will likely expose Wakanda's secret treasure, alert Thanos to the hidden location of the Soul Gem, and lead into Avengers: Infinity War, the next MCU movie.

* Which would neatly tie everything together, and provide a plausible rationalization for the ridiculous premise of "WTF, how did an African nation have such an advanced technology, more advanced than Western civilizations, but no one knows about it??"

Comment:
Hi
Just watched the Black Panther trailer 2, loved it, but I can‚Äôt help but think the music, to me, doesn‚Äôt represent what Black Panther embodies. We get the great cultural original clothing, we get the futuristic African society which also embraces tradition, yet when it comes to music I get more of a sense of western hip hop. 
I understand you want the film to appeal to an American audience when it comes to advertising and marketing, and that when we finally see the film it will do a great job of bringing a worthy soundtrack that will give the impression of a technologically advanced nation, whose music is also of a traditional source with added symbolism and blended to include their uniquely innovative diverse African culture.
Hopefully we can hear some of this in the next trailer to allay my apprehensions.
Thanks, What do you think?

Good twist Marvel.

I'm bummed because I was really looking forward to this.

Comment: My *ONLY* gripe is the music choice for the trailer. My God, rap music is not the *ONLY* music Black people listen to or identify with. Stereotype much? For the teaser trailer, it was fine because with teaser trailers you want to _hit people over the head_ with the visual as well as with the audio. Not only that, but the track they used in the teaser just fit so well with what the trailer was going for. But for this trailer, the music choice felt _forced_ . All of that "... _unhuh_ ..." and "... _Yeah_ ..." was completely out of place, IMO. I was hoping for something more epic sounding. Perhaps with some decidely African Drum-beats. Think *_Two Steps from Hell_* mixed with Kanye West's *_Love Lockdown_* . It actually belittles the trailer when they do stuff like this because it says this is how *ANYTHING*  _Black_ is seen to the........ people in charge of churning this stuff out. Which couldn't be farther from the truth.

Comment:
I know its a minor thing considering everything going on in the world, but did they have to use hip-hop for both trailers?

Thor: Ragnarok used Immigrant Song to show that one, this is a more irreverent take on Thor, and two, tie it more into the other cosmic Marvel film, Guardians of the Galaxy.

But Black Panther has been described as a "big, operatic family drama centered around a world of international espionage. So hopefully we‚Äôre getting the best of both worlds." As much as I loved Run The Jewels from the teaser, I don't feel like it fit the feel of the film, much like the music in this trailer.

As a both a MCU fan and a black guy, I'm excited for this film. But the inclusion of hip-hop feels like pandering.

Title: Marvel Studios' Black Panther - Official Trailer
Comment: I really love everything about this trailer, particularly the design of Wakanda, and its people. I know we saw something of that in the teaser, but this one seems to really reinforce it. Even the little details of the Dora Milaje's sort of "arms across the chest" salute, to what I have interpreted as a hip, young Wakandan's version of that, like a secret handshake of sorts that transpires between T'Challa and Shuri later in the trailer. I was also happy to see such a great female cast present here. Obviously we knew about Lupita, and Danai, but I was happy to see more of the Dora Milaje and their kickass armour. Shuri seems to be as intelligent and formidable as we hoped, and did I also see that Killmonger had a lady with him, helping him to jailbreak Klaue? I approve! Killmonger's suit looks lit too.
